a]]\n*Nigel Warren Green - [[Cello]]\n*Andy Findon - [[Flute]]\n*Bashira Johnson - [[Bell (instrument)|Bells]] & Percussion\n\n====\"That's Love, That It Is\"====\n\n*David Rhodes - Guitars\n*The Uptown Horns - Horns\n*[[Jerry Marotta]] & Bashira Johnson - Percussion\n*Background Voices - Tawaitha Agee, Brenda White, Vernice\n\n====\"Murder\"====\n\n*Malcolm Ross & David Rhodes - Guitars\n*Deepak Khazanchi - Sitar\n*[[Pandit Dinesh]] - Tablas\n*David McClymont - Bass Guitar\n*Dolette McDonald, Michelle Cobbs & [[Janice Pendarvis]] - Background voices\n\n====\"All Things Are Nice\"====\n\n*David Rhodes - Guitars\n*[[Pandit Dinesh]] - Tablas & Percussion\n*Dave Allen - Bass Guitar\n*Blair Cunningham - [[Hi-hat (instrument)|Hi-Hat]]\n\n====\"My Baby\"====\n\n*David Rhodes - Guitars\n*Jerry Marotta & Blair Cunningham - Percussion\n*The Uptown Horns - Horns\n*[[Neil Jason]] - Bass Guitar\n\n====\"The Day Before You Came\"====\n\n*[[Pandit Dinesh]] - Tablas\n*Deepak Khazanchi - [[Santoor]]\n*Sean Chadwick - [[Trumpet]] Solo\n\n==== The Uptown Horns Are ====\n\n*Joe Mosello - Trumpet\n*Vinnie Della-Rocca & Jim Clouse - [[saxophone]]s\n*Keith O\u2019Quinn & Jack Gale - [[Trombone]]\n*James Biondolillo - [[Maestro]]\n\n===Production===\n*Recorded at Marcus Music (London) and Sigma Sound (New York City). August\u2013November 1983\n*Produced by John Luongo<br/>\"Don't Tell Me\" produced by Peter Collins<br/>\"Game Above my Head\" produced by Blancmange & John Owen Williams\n*\"Time Became the Tide\" arranged by Linton Naiff & Blancmange\n*\"My Baby\" remixed by Dennis Weinrich & John Owen Williams\n*Engineered by Jay Mark in London. Femi Jiya assisted by Matt Wallis\n*Except \"Time Became the Tide\" recorded at Island Studios (London). Engineer: Richard Digby-Smith assisted by Steve Street\n*\"Don\u2019t Tell Me\" recorded at Sarm East (London). Engineer: Julian Mendlesohn\n*In New York. James Docherty, Michael Hutchinson, John Potaka\n*Assisted by Linda Randazzo, Jimmy Santis, Elisa Gura, Melanie West, Glenn Rosenstein\n*Design: M. Atkins & Marcx, Town & Country Planning\n*Management: Paul Smith & John Owen Williams\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|refs=\n<ref name=allmusic>{{cite web | first=Bill | last=Cassel | title=Review: Blancmange - ''Mange Tout'' | url={{Allmusic|class=album|id=r30825/review|pure_url=yes}} | work=[[Allmusic]] | publisher=[[Rovi Corporation]] | accessdate=15 June 2011 }}</ref>\n}}\n\n{{Blancmange}}\n\n[[Category:1984 albums]]\n[[Category:Blancmange (band) albums]]\n[[Category:Albums produced by Peter Collins (record producer)]]\n[[Category:London Records albums]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the album|other uses|Mange tout (disambiguation){{!}}Mange tout}}\n{{Infobox album\n| name       = Mange Tout\n| type       = studio\n| artist     = [[Blancmange (band)|Blancmange]]\n| cover      = Blancmange - Mange Tout.jpg\n| alt        =\n| released   = May 1984\n| recorded   = August\u2013November 1983\n| studio     =\n* Marcus Music, London{{efn|name=Except|Except \"Time Became the Tide\" and \"Don't Tell Me\"}}\n* [[Sigma Sound Studios|Sigma Sound]], New York City{{efn|name=Except}}\n* [[Island Studios|Island]], London{{efn|\"Time Became the Tide\"}}\n* [[Sarm East Studios|Sarm East]], London{{efn|\"Don't Tell Me\"}}\n| genre      =\n* [[New wave music|New wave]]\n* [[synth-pop]]\n| length     = 43:26\n| label      = [[London Records|London]]\n| producer   =\n* Blancmange\n* [[Peter Collins (record producer)|Peter Collins]]\n* John Luongo\n* John Owen Williams\n| prev_title = [[Happy Families (album)|Happy Families]]\n| prev_year  = 1982\n| next_title = [[Believe You Me]]\n| next_year  = 1985\n}}\n\n{{Album ratings\n| rev1 = [[AllMusic]]\n| rev1Score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref name=allmusic />\n| rev2 = ''[[Record Mirror]]''\n| rev2score = {{Rating|3|5}}<ref>{{cite magazine|last=Strike|first=Andy|date=19 May 1984|title=Albums|magazine=[[Record Mirror]]}}</ref>\n| rev3 = ''[[Smash Hits]]''\n| rev3score = {{Rating|9|10}}<ref name=\"Smash Hits\">{{cite magazine |first=Lisa |last=Anthony |title=Album Reviews: Blancmange \u2013 ''Mange Tout'' |magazine=[[Smash Hits]] |location=London |page=27 |date=10 May 1984}}</ref>\n}}\n\n'''''Mange Tout''''' is the second studio album by English [[synth-pop]] duo [[Blancmange (band)|Blancmange]], released in May 1984 by [[London Records]]. It was Blancmange's most successful album, peaking at number eight on the [[UK Albums Chart]]<ref name=\"ukchart\"/> and was certified Gold by the [[British Phonographic Industry]] (BPI) on 25 January 1985 for sales in excess of 100,000 copies.<ref name=\"BPI\"/> The album contained four UK top-40 singles, two of which reached the top 10.<ref name=\"officialcharts1\">{{cite web|url=http://www.officialcharts.com/artist/19533/blancmange/ |title=Blancmange {{!}} full Official Chart History |publisher=Official Charts Company |accessdate=22 October 2018}}</ref> The fourth single to be released and final track on the album is a cover version of [[ABBA]]'s song \"[[The Day Before You Came]]\".\n\nIn addition to the usual vinyl and cassette release, a limited-edition vinyl picture disc was also released. The album was later released on CD, and a remastered deluxe edition was released by [[Edsel]] in 2008, which featured a second disc of remixes and B-sides.\n\n==Track listing==\nAll songs written by [[Neil Arthur]] & [[Stephen Luscombe]], except where noted.\n\n===LP: SH 8554===\n\n====Side 1====\n# \"[[Don't Tell Me (Blancmange song)|Don't Tell Me]]\" \u2013 3:31\n# \"Game Above My Head\" \u2013 3:58\n# \"[[Blind Vision]]\" \u2013 3:56\n# \"Time Became the Tide\" \u2013 4:49\n# \"[[That's Love, That It Is]]\" \u2013 4:22\n\n====Side 2====\n# \"Murder\" \u2013 5:58\n# \"See the Train\" \u2013 2:04\n# \"All Things Are Nice\" \u2013 4:59\n# \"My Baby\" \u2013 3:59\n# \"[[The Day Before You Came]]\" ([[Benny Andersson|Andersson]]/[[Bj\u00f6rn Ulvaeus|Ulvaeus]]) \u2013 5:50\n\n===CD: 810 235\u20132===\n\n===2008 Edsel - Remastered CD: EDSL 2023===\n# \"Don't Tell Me\" \u2013 3:31\n# \"Game Above My Head\" \u2013 3:59\n# \"Blind Vision\" \u2013 3:59\n# \"Time Became The Tide\" \u2013 4:50\n# \"That's Love, That It Is\" \u2013 4:20\n# \"Murder\" \u2013 5:58\n# \"See The Train\" \u2013 2:05\n# \"All Things Are Nice\" \u2013 5:01\n# \"My Baby\" \u2013 3:57\n# \"[[The Day Before You Came]]\" \u2013 4:25 (Anderson/Ulvaeus)\n# \"Game Above My Head (Long Version)\" \u2013 7:14\n\n===2008 Edsel - The B-Sides And Remixes CD: EDSL 2023===\n# \"Blind Vision (Long Version)\" \u2013 9:39\n# \"Heaven Knows Where Heaven Is\" \u2013 3:24\n# \"On Our Way To?\" \u2013 5:37\n# \"That's Love, That It Is (Extended)\" \u2013 6:35\n# \"Vishnu (Full Length)\" \u2013 5:20\n# \"That's Love, That It Is (Remix)\" \u2013 7:34\n# \"Vishnu (Instrumental)\" \u2013 4:53\n# \"Don't Tell Me (Extended)\" \u2013 6:25\n# \"Get Out Of That\" \u2013 4:26\n# \"Feel Me (Live Version)\" \u2013 6:25\n# \"All Things Are Nice (Version)\" \u2013 4:14\n# \"[[The Day Before You Came]] (Extended)\" \u2013 7:59 (Anderson/Ulvaeus)\n\n==Personnel==\n\n===Musicians===\n*[[Neil Arthur]] - Voice, [[Drum]]s and [[Clarinet]]\n*[[Stephen Luscombe]] - [[Electronic keyboard|Electric Keyboards]], [[Piano]] and [[Trumpet]]\n\n===Additional musicians===\n\n====\"Don't Tell Me\"====\n\n*[[Pandit Dinesh]] - [[Tabla]] & Madal\n*Deepak Khazanchi - [[Sitar]]\n\n====\"Game Above My Head\"====\n\n*Bobby Collins - [[Bass guitar]]\n\n====\"Blind Vision\"====\n\n*[[David Rhodes (guitarist)|David Rhodes]] - [[Guitar]]s\n*The Uptown Horns - [[French horn|Horns]]\n*[[Neil Jason]] - Bass guitar\n*Bashira Johnson - [[Percussion instrument|percussion]]\n*Dolette McDonald, Brenda Jay Nelson & [[Jocelyn Brown]] - [[Backing vocals|Background voices]]\n\n====\"Time Became The Tide\"====\n\n*[[Gavyn Wright]] & Roy Gillard - [[Violin]]s\n*Garf Jackson - [[Viola]]\n*Nigel Warren Green - [[Cello]]\n*Andy Findon - [[Flute]]\n*Bashira Johnson - [[Bell (instrument)|Bells]] & Percussion\n\