apo Press|isbn=0-306-81136-7|ref=harv}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Davis |first=Angela Y. | authorlink = Angela Davis|year=1998 |title=Blues Legacies and Black Feminism: Gertrude \"Ma\" Rainey, Bessie Smith, and Billie Holiday |location=New York |publisher=Random House |isbn=0-679-77126-3}}\n* {{Cite book|last=Gourse|first=Leslie|authorlink=Leslie Gourse|year=2000|title=The Billie Holiday Companion: Seven Decades of Commentary|location=New York|publisher=Schirmer Trade Books|isbn=0-02-864613-4|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/billieholidaycom00gour_0}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Griffin |first=Farah Jasmine |year=2001 |title=If You Can't Be Free, Be A Mystery: In Search of Billie Holiday |location=New York |publisher=Random House |isbn=0-684-86808-3}}\n* {{Cite book |last1=Holiday |first1=Billie |first2=William |last2=Dufty |year=1957 |title=Lady Sings the Blues |location=New York |publisher=Doubleday |isbn=0-14-006762-0 |url=https://archive.org/details/ladysingsblues00holi_0 }}\n* {{Cite book |last=Ingham |first=Chris |year=2000 |title=Billie Holiday |location=Darby, Pennsylvania |publisher=Diane Publishing |isbn=1-56649-170-3}}\n* {{Cite book |last=James |first=Burnett |year=1984 |title=Billie Holiday |location=Gloucestershire, England |publisher=Spellmount Publishers |isbn=0-946771-05-7 |url=https://archive.org/details/billieholiday00jame }}\n* {{Cite news| last = Kaplan | first = Samuel W. | year = February 2002 | title = Strange Fruit | journal = [[Humanity & Society]] | volume = Volume 26, No. 1 | pages = 77\u201383}}\n* {{Cite video |last = Katz | first = Joel | year = 2002 | title =California Newsreel: Strange Fruit}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Millar |first=Jack |year=1994 |title=Fine and Mellow: A Discography of Billie Holiday |location=London |publisher=Billie Holiday Circle |isbn=1-899161-00-7}}\n* {{Cite book |last=Nicholson |first=Stuart |year=1995 |title=Billie Holiday |location=Boston |publisher=Northeastern University Press |isbn=1-55553-303-5}}\n* {{Cite boo